In the spirit of the ongoing Ramadan fasting, the minister of youth and sports development, Chief Sunday Dare, has donated a sienna car to Ogbomoso Progressive Forum, a wheelchair to a person living with disability and food items to the communities. He made the donation to the mammoth crowd that turned out to watch the minister (him) defeating Oyo Chapter of Sports Writers Association of Nigeria (SWAN) 6-2 in an exhibition table tennis match at the new sporting arena donated by the Minister to the people of Ogbomoso community. Notable personalities present at the occasion were former speaker of Oyo State House of Assembly, Hon. Gunju Ojo, DG FRIN, Professor Shola Adepoju, director of the National Institute of Sports (NIS), Professor Morónkólá, Registrar of the Federal Polytechnic Ayede, Dr. Adéwálé Akinsola, former director of grassroots development, Federal Ministry of Youth and Sports Development, Dr. Demola Arẹ and former director of Kwara State sports council, Mr Tunde Kazeem.